<li id="cite_note-weisenburger3-8"><b><a href="#cite_ref-weisenburger3_8-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWeisenburger1988">Weisenburger, Steven (1988). "Part 2: Un Perm au Casino Hermann Goering". <i>A Gravity's Rainbow Companion</i>. University of Georgia Press. pp.&#160;86, 105, 125–126, 152, 153, 291. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0820310263" class="internal">ISBN 0-8203-1026-3</a>.  "The number eight has a widespread significance throughout GR: there were eight episodes in part 2; Slothrop assumes eight different identities; V-E Day, White Lotos Day and Pynchon's birthday all fell on May 8; the text references Krishna, eighth avatar of Vishnu; and in Judaeo-Christianity eight is the number of letters in the Tetragrammaton."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Part+2%3A+Un+Perm+au+Casino+Hermann+Goering&amp;rft.atitle=A+Gravity%27s+Rainbow+Companion&amp;rft.aulast=Weisenburger&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven&amp;rft.au=Weisenburger%2C+Steven&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B86%2C+105%2C+125%26ndash%3B126%2C+152%2C+153%2C+291&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Georgia+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-8203-1026-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gravity%27s_Rainbow"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-weisenburger4-9"><b><a href="#cite_ref-weisenburger4_9-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWeisenburger1988">Weisenburger, Steven (1988). "Part 2: Un Perm au Casino Hermann Goering". <i>A Gravity's Rainbow Companion</i>. University of Georgia Press. pp.&#160;105. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0820310263" class="internal">ISBN 0-8203-1026-3</a>.  "The epigraph derives from a New York Times feature of September 21, 1969, entitled "How Fay Met Kong..."."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Part+2%3A+Un+Perm+au+Casino+Hermann+Goering&amp;rft.atitle=A+Gravity%27s+Rainbow+Companion&amp;rft.aulast=Weisenburger&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven&amp;rft.au=Weisenburger%2C+Steven&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B105&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Georgia+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-8203-1026-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gravity%27s_Rainbow"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-weisenburger5-10"><b><a href="#cite_ref-weisenburger5_10-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWeisenburger1988">Weisenburger, Steven (1988). "Part 3: In The Zone". <i>A Gravity's Rainbow Companion</i>. University of Georgia Press. pp.&#160;105. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0820310263" class="internal">ISBN 0-8203-1026-3</a>.  "Part 3 of the novel contains thirty-two episodes...because the gravitational pull...is a constant thirty-two feet per second and...because the number is significant in Kabbalistic mythology."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Part+3%3A+In+The+Zone&amp;rft.atitle=A+Gravity%27s+Rainbow+Companion&amp;rft.aulast=Weisenburger&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven&amp;rft.au=Weisenburger%2C+Steven&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B105&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Georgia+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-8203-1026-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gravity%27s_Rainbow"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.ham.muohio.edu/~krafftjm/pn/pn011.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.ham.muohio.edu/~krafftjm/pn/pn011.pdf" rel="nofollow"><i>Pynchon Notes</i> 11</a>, February 1983, p. 64.</li>
<li id="cite_note-weisenburger6-12"><b><a href="#cite_ref-weisenburger6_12-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFWeisenburger1988">Weisenburger, Steven (1988). "Introduction". <i>A Gravity's Rainbow Companion</i>. University of Georgia Press. pp.&#160;11. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0820310263" class="internal">ISBN 0-8203-1026-3</a>.  "the shape of Gravity's Rainbow is circular. The literary precursors of this design ... are Joyce's Finnegans Wake and Melville's ... The Confidence Man."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Introduction&amp;rft.atitle=A+Gravity%27s+Rainbow+Companion&amp;rft.aulast=Weisenburger&amp;rft.aufirst=Steven&amp;rft.au=Weisenburger%2C+Steven&amp;rft.date=1988&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B11&amp;rft.pub=University+of+Georgia+Press&amp;rft.isbn=0-8203-1026-3&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gravity%27s_Rainbow"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-tanner1-13"><b><a href="#cite_ref-tanner1_13-0" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFTanner1982">Tanner, T. (1982). "Gravity's Rainbow". <i>Thomas Pynchon</i>. London and New York: Methuen. pp.&#160;74. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0416316700" class="internal">ISBN 0-416-31670-0</a>.  "There are over 400 characters ... there are many discernible ... plots ... these plots touch and intersect, or diverge and separate."</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=bookitem&amp;rft.btitle=Gravity%27s+Rainbow&amp;rft.atitle=Thomas+Pynchon&amp;rft.aulast=Tanner&amp;rft.aufirst=T.&amp;rft.au=Tanner%2C+T.&amp;rft.date=1982&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B74&amp;rft.place=London+and+New+York&amp;rft.pub=Methuen&amp;rft.isbn=0-416-31670-0&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Gravity%27s_Rainbow"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
